    <string id="0">
        <![CDATA[In this chamber, the School of Magery kept their valued school mascot, 'Spiny.' When they abandoned the school, they left their mascot behind.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="1">
        <![CDATA[Unfortunately, their mascot, a long, vicious worm, is a very long lived creature. Feeding on the denizens of the school has helped it grow large, and it's imprisonment has put it in a very bad mood.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="6">
        <![CDATA[The copious amounts of virulent waste produced by the school's experiments were thrown into this portal. The waste disposal faculties were probably at the other end.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="7">
        <![CDATA[The portal is running on low power now, and is incapable of carrying anything anywhere. The waste here will just have to stay here.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="12">
        <![CDATA[You detect the too familiar burning scent of unprocessed School waste. Oh no. Not again.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="13">
        <![CDATA[You yank the lever. There's a brief grinding noise and the smell of smoke. Nothing else happens.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="14">
        <![CDATA[You hear the sound of portcullises opening. Or closing. You aren't sure.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="15">
        <![CDATA[Someone has carelessly left a note on top of this desk. It's brittle and yellowed with age, but still readable. "It is time. Get Palhatis and Pergaltho to Visitor's Quarters. I will do the rest. - Vinnia"]]>
    </string>
    <string id="16">
        <![CDATA[This book still contains notes on experiments carried out on this level. The most recent experiment listed regarded the development of a new acid creation spell. The listing mentions "High spill potential."]]>
    </string>
    <string id="17">
        <![CDATA[This book still contains notes on experiments carried out on this level. The most recent experiment listed regarded something called "Garment augmentation." Whatever that means.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="18">
        <![CDATA[This book still contains notes on experiments carried out on this level. The most recent experiment regarded the dissection of creatures called "Alien beasts."]]>
    </string>
    <string id="19">
        <![CDATA[The beasts were being kept in the holding cells on this level. The book mentions that care should be taken because of their "High escape potential."]]>
    </string>
    <string id="20">
        <![CDATA[You see the holding cells for the Experimentation Level. Unsurprisingly, considering how things have been going so far, whatever was living in here broke its way out some time ago, leaving rubble behind.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="21">
        <![CDATA[This exit is barred by two doors. They're standard issue heavy wooden doors, with a large padlock holding them closed. You try to get the padlock open, but even heavy blows don't affect it in the slightest.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="22">
        <![CDATA[Looks like yet another magical obstruction, and you don't have the key.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="23">
        <![CDATA[You find a pair of double doors, held shut with a large brass padlock. Fortunately, your brass key fits easily. You unlock the doors.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="24">
        <![CDATA[This double reinforced bunker holds the laboratories where the most dangerous and powerful experiments took place. A sour acidic smell reaches your sensitive adventurer's noses. There's been some sort of nasty spill.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="25">
        <![CDATA[You stand at a hidden rear exit of the School of Magery, a several mile long passage, lit by long-lasting magical lamps, which students and faculty could use to escape quickly, if necessary. The tunnel slopes gently up and out.]]>
    </string>
